parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe can cause the engine and transmission to fall out, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: and uneven tire wear. In severe cases
the subframe can be pushed through with a screwdriver
and the engine and transmission can fall out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the suspension and steering components can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents.
The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents.
symptoms: and the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and CVT can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
and the transmission or CVT fails to engage properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the frame and structural components can cause the vehicle to lose its structural integrity, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The frame and structural components show signs of rust and corrosion
and the vehicle may experience vibrations and noises while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the front and rear crossmembers can cause the vehicle's frame to weaken, leading to potential loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: and visible rust on the vehicle's undercarriage.
